      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## v0.1.4 — Internationalization, corpus organization & UX refinements\r\n  \r\n###  🌐 Internationalization (i18n)\r\n\r\n  The plugin now supports English and French. All UI strings are externalized into JSON locale files — the language can be changed in the setup wizard\r\n  or in Settings without restarting Obsidian. New wizard steps:\r\n  - Language — bilingual selection screen (EN/FR) shown before a language is chosen\r\n  - Storage — folder configuration with the recommended \"one vault per corpus\" workflow\r\n  \r\n###  📁 Corpus organization\r\n  \r\n  New command Organize corpus (Ctrl+P): define named classes (sub-folders) that are automatically mirrored across your transcriptions, mappings and\r\n  exports folders. When adding a transcription, you are prompted to choose a class.\r\n\r\n  ▎ We recommend one Obsidian vault per corpus — this keeps all associated files together and simplifies archiving.\r\n  \r\n###  ⚠️  Scope warning for name rules\r\n  \r\n  When creating or editing a rule for a first name, surname or full name with a folder or vault scope, a warning callout explains that this should only\r\n   be done for longitudinal approaches — to consistently track the same participant across transcriptions. A success callout confirms good practice\r\n  when file scope is used.\r\n\r\n###  📋 Mappings tab — grouped by scope\r\n\r\n  Rules in the Mappings panel are now displayed in three separate sections: File · Folder · Vault. A checkbox (checked by default) filters the view to\r\n  rules applicable to the active file only.\r\n\r\n###  🔧 Under the hood\r\n  \r\n  - WASM file access migrated from Node.js fs to vault.adapter — no filesystem access outside the Obsidian vault API\r\n  - README, CHANGELOG and ROADMAP now in English; French versions archived as *.fr.md\r\n  - EditRuleModal and QuickPseudonymizeModal fully internationalized\r\n\r\n  ---\r\n\r\n  Full changelog: CHANGELOG.md (https://github.com/core-hn/pseudobsidian-ization/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md)",
